[normal]The electrical Workforce.[bold]1[bold].[bold]Introduction.[bold]1[bold].1[bold] 
[normal]I’m Carl Bennett the Managing Director of 
[normal]Tradeskills4U[bold] Ltd[bold]. We are the UK's largest educator of the electrical installation adult workforce and the country’s only specialist electrical IET ‘Centre of Excellence’, to put this into context, we
[normal]’re
[normal] actually a modest family run company employ
[normal]ing 
[normal]30 people. 
[normal]1[bold].2[bold] 
[normal]Wh
[normal]at we are is a business to business company with an enviable reputation and 98% 
[normal]candidate 
[normal]approval rating. We are an independent company; 
[normal]none
[normal] funded organization. Chairman Clive Betts MP and other MPs have visited our facilities.
[normal]1[bold].3[bold] 
[normal]We train approximatel
[normal]y
[normal] 
[normal]3000 adult candidates each year in a full range of electrical domestic, commercial and industrial skills and adult vocational qualifications, many for continuing professional development. We also train adult apprentices and Domestic electrical installers
[normal] to enable them to register on the various Competent Person’s Schemes. 
[normal]1.4[bold] 
[normal]Our core candidates are 
[normal]75%[bold] existing electrical and other trade’s contractors and 
[normal]25%[bold] new entrants.  
[normal]95 %[bold] of our candidates are micro business owners and employers, essentially the
[normal] backbone of the industry. 
[normal]1[bold].5[bold] 
[normal]Like any good business, we constantly engage with our customers/candidates. Dozens are literally under our roof every day, many of them are electrical contractors and others not fully qualified electricians but are employed 
[normal]within the greater electrical industry because of their ability to work within the Competent Person Schemes, they have a wide range of experience in many other trades and also have competency in electrical installation to undertake that role as their main 
[normal]occupation 
[normal]requires I.e. Heating engineers, kitchen fitters, home maintenance contractors, auto gate installers, gas engineer
[normal]s
[normal], the list is too numerous to be exhaustive within this space
[normal]1[bold].6[bold] 
[normal]As M
[normal]D
[normal] it’s my job to gather evidence, engage with and listen to 
[normal]opinions from every aspect of the wider industry of electrical installation to ensure we supply the right training, qualifications and skills options for employers, electricians, associated trades, companies and new entrants into the industry. 
