[normal]a)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The
[normal] IET[bold] (Institution of Engineering Technology), o
[normal]ne of the world's largest organisations for engineers and technicians who have warned that proposed reforms to government funding could lead to a reduction in UK apprenticeships. We agree with IET claims 
[normal]that the reforms are likely to reduce quality and deter SMEs from taking part in apprenticeship schemes and have criticised apprenticeship reforms, saying that the changes would incur higher costs that may prevent smaller businesses from taking on apprenti
[normal]ces.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]b)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The 
[normal]Edge Foundation[bold], a leading independent education charity, pointed to the government's own research that suggests apprentice numbers could fall by 
[normal]73%[bold] when employers have to pay at least half the cost.
