[normal]our adult workforce to better reflect small employer’s needs. 
[normal]Our op
[normal]inion is that at the moment they do not.
[normal]3[bold]. [bold]Shortage of workforce supply.[bold]3[bold].1[bold] 
[normal]It may surprise you to learn that the person that comes to your door to undertake some electrical work for you in your home is almost certainly going to be a 
[normal]properly qualified 
[normal]Competent Person and a member of a Competent Person Scheme. They are probably u
[normal]nlikely to be a so called ‘fully qualified electrician’. (That is a contractor who has served a full time traditional apprenticeship with a full set of qualifications
[normal] i.e a Level 3 NVQ plus other qualifications
[normal]) This is a fact that surprises many existing 
[normal]electrical contractors who wrongly assume the ‘fully qualified electrician’ to be in the majority.
[normal] It is certainly our experience that 
[normal]an increasing majority of 
[normal]electricians are ‘fully qualified’
[normal],
[normal] many hav
[normal]ing
[normal] failed to keep up with current regulations, tec
[normal]hnologies and changes in 
[normal]best 
[normal]practices
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]4[bold]. [bold]Competent Persons keep the system [bold]working.[bold]4[bold].1[bold] 
[normal]It is o
[normal]ur estimation
[normal],
[normal] gained from experience of the thousands of small contractor companies with whom we engage and is compatible with
[normal] many electrical education and workforce reports I have seen and other business and training leaders in our sector
[normal] we
[normal] have spoken
[normal] with
[normal] that
[normal] less than 
[normal]50%[bold] of people who undertake electrical work in this country are what you might call ‘fully qualified elect
[normal]ricians’, the remainder are likely to be properly trained, qualified and experienced Competent Persons with a wide range of experience in many other trades who also have competency in electrical installations to undertake that role as their main occupation
[normal] requires and I
[normal] have
[normal] no 
[normal]evidence to 
[normal]doubt 
[normal]they 
[normal]do a proper and safe job.  
[normal]4[bold].2[bold] 
[normal]Frankly if it were not for Competent Persons undertaking electrical work by the tens of thousands, the electrical infrastructure of this country would be compromised and poorly 
[normal]serviced. There are not enough so called ‘fully qualified electricians’
[normal]. Many more experienced 
[normal]in the industry 
[normal]than me I have heard
