[normal]&#xa0;[bold]5[bold].[bold] The entry routes for employment in the electrical industry are ‘not fit for purpose’[bold].[bold]5.1[bold] 
[normal]The purpose of apprenticeships and career routes into the industry are to secure and train the future workforce for the benefit of us all. 
[normal]They are not working as they should and this is relevant for your committee to consider because electrical workforce that operates under Part P is set to dwindle rapidly in coming years. 
[normal]5.2[bold] 
[normal]From a training provider’s perspective,
[normal] a single qualification s
[normal]ystem to enter the industry is ‘not fit for purpose’. 
