[normal]&#xa0;[bold]6[bold]. [bold]Competent Persons qualification v Full NVQ [bold]qualification[bold].[bold]6[bold].1[bold] 
[normal]The training for full NVQ, please note, 
[normal]the training
[normal], i.e 
[normal] the skills and knowledge that a person is taught in a college
[normal], not the 
[normal]workbased a
[normal]ssessment 
[normal]and gathering of experience 
[normal]which follows
[normal] 
[normal]training
[normal],
[normal] commonly called ‘an apprenticeship’.
[normal]6[bold].2[bold] The typical 
[normal]delivery of
[normal] training
[normal] in centre by 
[normal]and
[normal] FE 
[normal]College
[normal] is one day a week for 3 years. For easy comparison if you took the same course full time, it would be of 16 weeks duration
[normal]6[bold].3[bold] 
[normal]This covers everything from installation of sockets 
[normal]in your home 
[normal]to 
[normal]the 
[normal]substati
[normal]on
[normal] down the road
[normal], domestic, commercial and industrial
[normal]. H
[normal]owever it’s a one size fits all 
[normal]and is designed for a 16-19 year old with zero transferable skills from other work experience. 
[normal]6[bold].4[bold] 
[normal]The Domestic electrical element within an apprenticeship qualification is of 8 weeks duration; again assuming you did it as full time training. 
[normal]6[bold].5[bold] 
[normal]By no coincidence the new 
[normal]qualification 
[normal]‘Level 3 certificate in Installing, Testing and Ensuring Compliance
[normal] of Electrical Installations in Dwellings’ 
[normal]that enables a person to become a Competent person comprises of 12 weeks full time 
[normal]training
[normal], so well over and above that of an 
[normal]NVQ
[normal] qualification.
[normal]6[bold].6[bold] 
[normal]The assumption that Domestic Competency training is somehow inf
[normal]erior to a Full 
[normal]NVQ
[normal] is incorrect and misinformed. The training for the Domestic element is equal if not superior. Also usually because the demographic for this qualification is a 24+ years adult and they bring other relevant skills with them
[normal],
[normal] their compete
[normal]ncy is likely to be higher
