[normal]&#xa0;[bold]8[bold]. [bold]Our suggestion of a Domestic Electrician Grade to ensure constant supply of workforce and progression entry [bold]into industry.[bold]&#xa0;[bold]8[bold].1[bold] 
[normal]The one size fits all 
[normal]route into the industry
[normal] is flawed, too expensive and too 
[normal]challenging for the person for which it is intended 
[normal]. We suggest there should be properly understood and accepted multi grades of electricians. Each capable 
[normal]of progressing to the higher level above.
[normal] 
[normal]W
[normal]e suggest an additional grade of electrician 
[normal]to sit 
[normal]between the Competent person and the Full NVQ Qualified electrician as below. 
[normal]8[bold].2[bold] 
[normal]This would have the advantage of people entering the industry with a 
[normal]qualification based on what job they would actually be doing
[normal] and 
[normal]then provides a 
[normal]manageable
[normal] 
[normal]and
[normal] cost effective stepping stone to progression for the Full qualification
[normal] and by design naturally upgrades safety &amp; best 
[normal]practice
[normal]. 
[normal]8[bold].3[bold] 
[normal]We suggest three grades of
[normal] persons allowed to undertake electrical work. 
[normal]Each grade capable of progression.
[normal]   
[normal]Grades
[normal] in 
[normal]ascending 
[normal]order
[normal],
[normal]   
[normal]C[bold]. 
[normal]Competent Domestic Electrical Installer.
[normal] For allied 
[normal]trades,
[normal] Heating engineer etc. 
[normal] (As exists but with proper industry recognition
[normal] and mandatory registration
[normal])
[normal] [bold]B[bold]. 
[normal]The Domestic Electrician. Domestic only work. (A shorter more defined competence qualification to better reflect the role, based on achievement not length)
[normal]A[bold]. 
[normal]The Approved 
[normal]Electrician (
[normal]Comprising of Domestic, Commercial and
[normal] Industrial) 
